den auf die Konstruktionen des Eigenen zurückzuschließen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aSocial perception. 0aStereotypes (Social psychology). 0aStigma (Social psychology). 4aKultursoziologie. 4aSozialität. 4aSoziologie. 4aSoziologische Theorie. 4aStigmatisierung. 4aWissenssoziologie. 4a»Othering«. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aSociological Theory.  aSociology of Culture.  aSociology of Knowledge.  aSociology.0 cprintz978393312784640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839400845?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839400845zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839400845/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA